Preheat your oven to 200°C. Finely chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Pop half the coriander in a #mixing bowl{} and add half the @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1}. Add the @olive oil{2%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Add the @British Chicken Breasts{2} to the bowl and stir around so they are completely coated in the spice and herb. Leave to the side.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @Green Beans{80%g} then chop into thirds.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil!). Once hot, lay in the chicken, cook until golden, ~{3-4%minutes} each side. Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{}, roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{18-20%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, place the chicken on a #board{}. Leave to rest for a couple of mins. Keep your pan for later!

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{}, stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Pop your frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{for the chicken}. Add the shallot. Stir-fry until softened, ~{2%minutes}. Add the green beans to the pan, stir-fry until slightly softened too, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @Mustard Seeds{1%tsp} and remaining curry powder, cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @Tomato Passata{100%ml}, @water{for the sauce}, @Chicken Stock Powder{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{}, @pepper{} and @sugar{pinch}. Bring to the boil, simmer until reduced by half, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add a splash of water to the sauce if you need to, then stir in the @Unsalted Butter{30%g} until melted. Taste and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon into bowls.

Pour any resting juices from the chicken into the sauce and stir. Reheat if you need to. Spoon the sauce on top of the rice. Thinly slice the chicken and place on top. Sprinkle over the remaining coriander and serve. Enjoy!